# WeChat Mini Program Frontend Project Rules

You are an expert developer specializing in WeChat Native Mini Programs using TypeScript. You must adhere to the following strict technical, architectural, and encoding guidelines for this project.

## 1. Encoding & Language Guardrails (CRITICAL)
- **NO UNICODE ESCAPING:** You must write all Chinese characters as raw, literal, human-readable text (e.g., use "й≤ЬиК±" or "з°ЃиЃ§еЕ•еЇУ"). **NEVER** convert Chinese strings or comments into Unicode escape sequences (like `\u7e6a\u5236`).
- **FILE ENCODING:** Always save and output files using the standard UTF-8 encoding.
- **PATCHING DISCIPLINE:** When generating or refactoring files that are brand new or contain heavy text/configuration changes, prefer outputting the **whole file content** instead of incremental chunks to avoid "patch not assignable" errors.

## 2. Architecture & Backend Integration Constraints
- **NO WECHAT CLOUD DEVELOPMENT (дЇСеЉАеПС):** This project **DOES NOT** use WeChat CloudBase, Cloud Functions, or Cloud Databases.
- **SELF-HOSTED BACKEND:** All data features interact with our self-hosted Next.js full-stack backend via HTTPS network requests.
- **API ROUTE STANDARDS:** Business requests use `utils/request.ts` (base: `/api/miniprogram`). WeChat login uses `utils/wechat-auth.ts` (`/api/wechat/auth/login`).
  - Base URL maps to the Next.js service: `http://localhost:3000/api/miniprogram` (or LAN IP for physical device testing).
  - Main endpoints include: `/homepage`, `/products`, `/recommendations`, `/home-scene-entries`, `/orders`, `/cart`, `/recipients`.

## 3. WeChat Native TypeScript Coding Standards
- **FILE STRUCTURE:** Every page or component must strictly consist of four parallel files with matching names:
  - `.wxml` (Structure - raw XML tags like `<view>`, `<text>`, `<image>`, `<scroll-view>`)
  - `.wxss` (Styles - native utility classes or standard CSS)
  - `.json` (Configuration - explicit definitions for `usingComponents`, `navigationBarTitleText`, etc.)
  - `.ts` (Logic - strict TypeScript typing using official WeChat Mini Program type definitions)
- **PAGE & COMPONENT INITIALIZATION:**
  - Initialize pages using `Page({...})` and components using `Component({...})`.
  - Always enforce explicit Type Casting for events and datasets if needed.
  - Implement standard lifecycle methods accurately (`onLoad`, `onShow`, `onReady` for pages).
- **DATA BINDING:** Use `this.setData({ ... })` synchronously to trigger UI rerenders. Never mutate `this.data` directly.

## 4. Specific Business Logic Guidelines (Flower Studio)
- **DYNAMIC CATEGORIES:** Category lists on the homepage or navigation pages must be loaded dynamically from `request({ url: '/homepage' })`. Do not hardcode any product categories in the frontend.
- **MULTIPLE CATEGORIES PROCESSING:** Expect `product.category` from the backend to arrive as an array of strings (`string[]`). Ensure UI rendering accounts for products belonging to multiple categories concurrently.
- **OUT OF STOCK HANDLING:** Always inspect `product.isOutOfStock` or total stock counters. If a product is out of stock, render a elegant, blurred overlay mask (`дїКжЧ•еФЃзљД / еПѓйҐДзЇ¶жШОжЧ•`) and disable the immediate purchase buttons.
- **LOGISTICS & DELIVERY FORM:** Checkout page requires specialized fields: `deliveryTime` (Picker component for date/time), `receiverName`, `receiverPhone`, `deliveryAddress`, and a custom text area for `greetingCard` (иіЇеН°з•Эз¶Пиѓ≠).

## 5. UI & Aesthetics
- Maintain a premium, high-end floral studio visual style. Use minimalist layouts, generous white spaces, low-saturation elegant color schemes, and large high-definition images.